"v.换羽，脱毛；n.换羽(期)，脱毛(期) 【英】 换羽,脱毛(lose most of its feathers, hair, or fur at the season when a new covering for the body grows)换羽(期),脱毛(期)(t he time of molting) 【考】 molt : bird / slough : snake(鸟脱羽/蛇脱皮)molt : feathers / shed : hair(脱羽是脱去羽毛/脱 发是脱去头发)反义词：fledge(长羽 毛) 【例】 molt one's old notions(去掉旧观念) v. /n. 换羽, 脱毛, 蜕皮 【记】读: 摸他, 总是摸他的头就会变成秃子－脱发 【类】molt: bird = slough: snake鸟脱羽 = 蛇脱皮molt: feathers = shed: hair脱羽是脱去羽毛 = 假发是脱去头发 【反】fledge(v 长羽毛) 【记】音：毛脱；音：模特，模特总是不停地换衣服 molt (v.)  also moult, mid-14c., mouten, of feathers, ""to be shed,"" from Old English *mutian ""to change"" (in bemutian ""to exchange""), from Latin mutare ""to change"" (see mutable). Transitive sense, of birds, ""to shed feathers"" is first attested 1520s. With parasitic -l-, late 16c., on model of fault, etc. Related: Molted, moulted; molting, moulting. As a noun from 1815."
